records.addlTxt: Defendant accepted into FOP; contract will terminate on January 14, 2023

The Court held a colloquy with the defendant prior to approving his waiver of counsel to ensure he was waiving his rights competently, deliberately, and voluntarily.  The court apprised the defendant of his right to counsel, of the advantages of counsel, and of the difficulties and disadvantages of self-representation.  The Court also apprised the defendant of the nature and elements of the charges and the range of possible penalties upon entry of a guilty plea.  Based on this colloquy, the Court approved the defendants waiver of counsel.

Plea Questionnaire & Waiver of Rights Signed. Def entered a plea of guilty to count 2. Count 1 is dismissed. Court accepted def's plea but w/h adjudication and referred def to FOP. Bail continued.
Status conference on June 22, 2022 at 09:15 am.
Court printed a copy of the information for the DE. Court entered not guilty plea for defendant. Motions due 20 days. Bail continued.

Defendant appeared without counsel.  Frank John Remington appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DE filed a waiver to counsel form. Court reviewed the form with the DE. Witness M.M. sworn and testified. Direct exam by the State. Venue established. DE identified. No cross. Witness excused. Court made findings and probable cause found.
Preliminary hearing on April 12, 2022 at 08:30 am.

09:42 AM Defendant appeared.  Timothy Robert Verhoff appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DE not eligible for SPD & needs to complete CDP application process.  CT advises DE of right to atty.  Bail cont'd; set PH in 2 weeks. DE given notice in hand.
Status conference on March 29, 2022 at 09:30 am.
